  focus: "This lesson examines how S106 viability review mechanisms — particularly overage/clawback clauses and deferred contribution triggers — operate in practice for housing association-led residential schemes. Understanding these mechanisms is critical for APC candidates because they directly affect scheme viability, affordable housing delivery, and the negotiation dynamics between RPs, LPAs, and landowners.",
